of Rehob, king of Zobah, as he went to recover his border at the river Euphrates.","year":-1040},{"id":"rechWgxyZnSoCILIt","ref":"2Sam.8.4","text":"And David took from him a thousand chariots, and seven hundred horsemen, and twenty thousand footmen: and David houghed all the chariot horses, but reserved of them for an hundred chariots.","year":-1040},{"id":"recTuVFDEoHYs2c2p","ref":"2Sam.8.5","text":"And when the Syrians of Damascus came to succour Hadadezer king of Zobah, David slew of the Syrians two and twenty thousand men.","year":-1040},{"id":"recz2GWH2Z5rSlxhC","ref":"2Sam.8.6","text":"Then David put garrisons in Syria of Damascus: and the Syrians became servants to David, and brought gifts. And the LORD preserved David whithersoever he went.","year":-1040},{"id":"recCvALi3A9yQiZlS","ref":"2Sam.8.7","text":"And David took the shields of gold that were on the servants of Hadadezer, and brought them to Jerusalem.","year":-1040},{"id":"recTNdfpKFXd0Lcu8","ref":"2Sam.8.8","text":"And from Betah, and from Berothai, cities of Hadadezer, king David took exceeding much brass.","year":-1040}]}
